&lt;p&gt;Market changes, competitor dynamics, changing technology, change in workforce are just some changes that businesses experience. This results in increased complexity and uncertainty @Work! Leaders of organizations must deliver more, innovative products and services on a more frequent basis in order to survive and thrive. This webinar is centered around the topic of &lt;strong&gt;Agile Leadership&lt;/strong&gt; to help navigate this ever-changing landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Srikrishna Joshi&lt;/strong&gt;, SAFe Program, Consultant 4.0, TBR, CSP, CSM, CSPO, PMI ACP, PMP, CAL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Krishna has facilitated 100+ training sessions on Scrum, Agile, Scaled Agile Frameworks for close to 1500+ participants. Krishna is a successful Enterprise agile leader, Coach/Trainer with the 18+ years of industrial experience while working with Servicenow, PegaSystems, IBM, CA Technologies, CSC, Tech Mahindra, NTT Data and extensively travelled on Consulting/Business Development and Scrum, Agile, Scaled Agile Consulting assignments in India, US, UK, Ukraine. He has played multiple leadership consulting roles over the past decade, as a consultant, agile transformation coach, Program/Portfolio Manager for delivery, Pre-sales manager, Test Manager, Business Transition Manager, Business Analyst, Consulting Leader, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Our world is changing and changing fast. The original paradigm of education as we know it is quickly getting obsolete as the fundamental assumptions of the &amp;lsquo;why&amp;rsquo;, &amp;lsquo;what&amp;rsquo;, &amp;lsquo;how&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;where&amp;rsquo; of education are getting questioned and attacked from all sides - especially from the industry, one of the most&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;important stakeholders. Education space (and specifically EdTech) is happening and happening big in India with lot of established large and medium companies, startups and entrepreneurs investing in the space. This space has the potential, especially in a fast-developing country like India with the urgent need to augment the education space where fairly large gaps have been seen after systematic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;investment by government and the traditional private educational enterprises. Listen in to an early start up story from Abhilash Joseph, who will talk about current trends &amp;amp; opportunities, gaps, funding potential, risks and his experience in general.&lt;/p&gt;
